what happens , step by step

your dockerfile build the image in 3 stages:

stage 1- Build the frontend (the website)
. takes your React code in frontend
. run npm run build (vite) ,which turns all your react code into plain sattic file:HTML,JS,CSS
.these land in frontend/dist/
.THe public clerk key gets baked into th js here (VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY)

stage2 - BUild the backend(the API)
. Takes your Express code in backend
.npm run build here literally just copies src/-> dist/ (backend is plain JS, npthing to compile)

stage3 - The final runtime  image (the only one that ships)
.installs only production dependencies(no dev tool, keeps the image small)
.copies the backend code->dist/
.starts the server with node dist/index.js